WEBVTT

1
00:02:44.986 --> 00:02:47.853
<i>This is the universe.</i>

2
00:02:47.948 --> 00:02:49.655
<i>Big, isn't it?</i>

3
00:02:51.201 --> 00:02:54.990
<i>Thousands of suns, myriads of stars,</i>

4
00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:57.822
<i>separated by immense distances</i>

5
00:02:57.916 --> 00:03:00.533
<i>and by thin, floating clouds of gas.</i>

6
00:03:01.628 --> 00:03:04.461
<i>The starlight makes the gas transparent,</i>

7
00:03:04.548 --> 00:03:06.539
<i>and where there are no stars,</i>

8
00:03:06.633 --> 00:03:09.466
<i>it appears as dark, obscuring clouds,</i>

9
00:03:10.429 --> 00:03:13.046
<i>like that great black cone over there.</i>

10
00:03:15.809 --> 00:03:18.927
<i>Hello. There's a nova.</i>

11
00:03:19.020 --> 00:03:21.887
<i>A whole solar system exploded.</i>

12
00:03:21.982 --> 00:03:24.940
<i>Someone must have been messing about
with the uranium atom.</i>


13
00:03:25.777 --> 00:03:29.361
<i>No, it's not our solar system,
I'm glad to say.</i>


14
00:03:36.246 --> 00:03:40.581
<i>Ah, those are called
a globular cluster of stars.</i>


15
00:03:41.585 --> 00:03:43.075
<i>Rather fine.</i>

16
00:03:49.134 --> 00:03:51.375
<i>Down here in the right-hand corner,</i>

17
00:03:51.470 --> 00:03:54.132
<i>see that little chap
rather like a Boy Scout's badge?</i>


18
00:03:55.015 --> 00:03:58.849
<i>It's a mass of gas expanding
at thousands of cubic miles a minute.</i>


19
00:04:08.028 --> 00:04:10.941
<i>Ah, here we are.
We 're getting near a home.</i>


20
00:04:11.031 --> 00:04:13.819
