Come on, fellows, break it up.
Spread out here.


157
00:14:03.998 --> 00:14:05.614
Room with bath.

158
00:14:05.708 --> 00:14:08.496
- Oh, uh, do you have USO shows here?
- No, we don't.


159
00:14:08.586 --> 00:14:10.202
Okay, we'll stay.

160
00:14:11.172 --> 00:14:14.085
- Officer's quarters, of course.
- We're all the same up here, Captain.


161
00:14:14.634 --> 00:14:17.501
Excuse me... brother.

162
00:14:24.769 --> 00:14:26.555
Take over.

163
00:14:27.730 --> 00:14:31.314
- I wish I could make a phone call.
- From here? That would be long distance.


164
00:14:32.026 --> 00:14:34.518
- Flying Officer Trubshawe?
- Oh, I'm so sorry.


165
00:14:34.612 --> 00:14:36.353
You can't wait here any longer.

166
00:14:36.447 --> 00:14:38.438
You must be mistaken about your captain.

167
00:14:38.533 --> 00:14:41.867
- Well, if anyone's mistaken, it's not me.
- Mistakes don't happen here.


168
00:14:41.953 --> 00:14:44.115
But this is the aircrew section, isn't it?

169
00:14:44.205 --> 00:14:45.695
You should know.

170
00:14:45.790 --> 00:14:47.781
Peter couldn't have got away with it.

171
00:14:50.837 --> 00:14:52.877
Besides, you checked
his invoice for me, didn't you?


172
00:14:52.922 --> 00:14:55.505
Yes. It was against the regulations.

173
00:14:56.217 --> 00:14:58.709
Regulations are made to be broken.

174
00:14:58.803 --> 00:15:02.467
He was due here half an hour after me. This
is his section, and he hasn't reported.


175
00:15:02.557 --> 00:15:05.549
So he's either AWOL
or there's been a mistake.


176
00:15:05.643 --> 00:15:08.180
There hasn't been a mistake here
for a thousand years.


177
00:15:08.729 --> 00:15:11.471
Oh! So there have been mistakes?

178
00:15:11.566 --> 00:15:15.059
The girl that was here before me,
she was here 640 years.


179
00:15:15.153 --> 00:15:16.268
